The campus is so full of life.
There are students rushing to their classes, practicing
magic in the main field and reading against a tree with
some notebooks.
This will be home for the next several years.
Looking at your schedule, your first class takes place
in the Observatory for Herbalism with Professor Arcane.
SchoolFace_Image
Walking inside, it's a bit humid but the warmth is
welcome as you remove your coats in the locker area.
There is a set of large stained wooden doors that lead
you through in a beautiful dome filled with trees,
flowers, herbs, and hanging chandeliers scattered
throughout different areas to provide more light than
the current natural light.
It's massive in here and you walk along the red stone
walkways where you see different signs for directions.
You see first years listed and continue through the
pathways. The air is so sweet and fresh and it's almost
energizing to breathe it in.
You walk past a few of the other years designated areas
were you see individual greenhouses no larger than a
double sized garden shed. There are lush plants growing
out of each of them from where you can see and their
class year areas are full of life. It's pristine and
well kept - not a single spec of dirt out of place.
All the students have started their lesson for the day
and you find the archway for Year One students. You see
there are more greenhouses and they're occupied with
busy students. Standing against a large table in the
center of the space is a tall man, with a lean build,
and his hair is pulled back into a lose pony tail.
He's wearing black dress pants, white dress shirt, and
black vest with the arms rolled up his forearms.
There's a white flower in his vest pocket and you see
he's wearing black gloves and seems to be reviewing
some documentation. There's a cup beside him and
approaching closer you see there is an herbal tea
steeping inside. He looks up and gives a slight smile.
